  "text": "According to the clinical features of the patients in the earthquake and non-earthquake groups, we found that the age distributions in both groups were similar, but there were significantly more patients with ages ranging from 20-50 years old in the non-earthquake group. Additionally, male patients were also more common in the non-earthquake group than in the earthquake group. These differences were consistent with previous reports. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] This difference possibly reflects the tendency of young and middle-aged male patients to engage in riskier social behaviors.",
